{"seq": 5, "ts": "2026-04-22T05:06:27.711890+00:00", "event": "agent_message", "source": "Analyst", "message_type": "TextMessage", "content": "## Dataset Summary\n\n### Shape\n- **Rows:** 5,110\n- **Columns:** 12\n\n### Data Types\n\n| Column | Data Type | Description |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| id | int64 | Unique identifier |\n| gender | str | Categorical (Male/Female) |\n| age | float64 | Continuous (0.08 - 82.0 years) |\n| hypertension | int64 | Binary (0/1) |\n| heart_disease | int64 | Binary (0/1) |\n| ever_married | str | Categorical (Yes/No) |\n| work_type | str | Categorical |\n| Residence_type | str | Categorical (Urban/Rural) |\n| avg_glucose_level | float64 | Continuous |\n| bmi | float64 | Continuous (Body Mass Index) |\n| smoking_status | str | Categorical |\n| stroke | int64 | **Target** - Binary (0/1) |\n\n### Missing Values\n- Only **bmi** has missing values: 201 out of 5,110 (~3.9%)\n- All other columns are complete\n\n### Key Observations\n1. **Class Imbalance:** The target variable `stroke` is highly imbalanced - only 4.87% of records indicate stroke (1), while 95.13% are non-stroke (0)\n2. **Age Range:** Spans from infants (0.08 years) to elderly (82 years)\n3. **BMI Range:** 10.3 to 97.6 with mean ~28.9\n4. **Features Mix:** Contains both numerical (age, glucose, bmi) and categorical (gender, work_type, smoking_status) predictors\n\nThis is a healthcare dataset suitable for binary classification to predict stroke risk based on demographic and health indicators.\n\nTERMINATE", "created_at": "2026-04-22 05:06:27.710312+00:00"}
